description: After winning the license to publish a Worzel Gummidge strip away from IPC's Look-In, Marvel UK launched a monthly Worzel Gummidge magazine in 1982. Stylistically, it was in a similar vein to Doctor Who Magazine, perhaps because Marvel UK creators believed that since actor Jon Pertwee, who played Worzel, had also played the third Doctor, they could entice the same readership to pick up their new title. Low sales indicated they had misjudged their target audience, and Worzel Gummidge was cancelled within a year and replaced by a weekly Worzel Gummidge title aimed at a slightly younger readership.
name: Worzel Gummidge
